3️⃣ What is MapStruct?
MapStruct is a Java library that automatically converts (maps) one object into another — usually:

👉 Entity ⇄ DTO

It generates mapping code at compile time, so you don’t have to write manual conversion logic.

🧠 Simple Definition

MapStruct is a compile-time bean mapper that generates type-safe mapping code automatically.

🎯 Why MapStruct Exists

Without MapStruct, developers write manual mapping:

dto.setId(user.getId());
dto.setName(user.getName());
dto.setEmail(user.getEmail());

This becomes repetitive and error-prone.

MapStruct removes this boilerplate.

⚙️ How MapStruct Works

You only write an interface:

@Mapper(componentModel = "spring")
public interface UserMapper {

    UserDto toDto(User user);

    User toEntity(UserDto dto);
}

✅ That’s it.

During compilation, MapStruct automatically generates:

@Component
public class UserMapperImpl implements UserMapper {

    @Override
    public UserDto toDto(User user) {
        if (user == null) return null;

        UserDto dto = new UserDto();
        dto.setId(user.getId());
        dto.setName(user.getName());
        dto.setEmail(user.getEmail());

        return dto;
    }
}

You never write this code manually.

🚀 Key Features
✅ Compile-Time Code Generation

No reflection

Very fast execution

Errors caught during compilation

✅ Spring Boot Integration
@Mapper(componentModel = "spring")

Mapper becomes a Spring Bean:

@Autowired
private UserMapper mapper;
✅ Automatic Field Mapping

If field names match:

name → name
email → email

MapStruct maps automatically.

✅ Custom Mapping Support
@Mapping(source = "email", target = "userEmail")
UserDto toDto(User user);
✅ Collection Mapping
List<UserDto> toDtoList(List<User> users);

No loops needed.

⚡ Why MapStruct Is Popular in Spring Boot
